Editorial: See you at FidoCon '91!
Tom Jennings

This is a special, truncated FidoNews, published on Wednesday, instead
of Sunday, since the entire editorial staff (doesn't that sound officious?)
is off to FidoCon in about seven hours. Tim Pozar and I will be driving
out in my ancient Rambler, searching out LPG sources along the way (it's
not so bad, actually, and I just did this very thing only a few weeks ago).

ANYWAYS -- to reiterate something I mentioned weeks ago -- FidoNews needs
your writeups on FidoCon. If you are attending, please if you can bear it,
write about what you see -- sessions attended, rumors heard, decisions
made, products seen, fights, events like the annual hard-disk toss (it gets
easier and easier every year... in 1980 it would have been Shugart 14"
fixed Winchesters... this year it's probably a 2.5" somethingorother).
Chances are, if you sat through the whole thing it's probably of
excuciating interest to someone else. Tell the world! (Well, our corner of
it.)

Read ARTSPEC.DOC, it's not very demanding, and mail 'em in! Bye!


