By David French, 1:103/950
FidoNews Version List Notification...

It has been brought to my attention in some of the Fido Echos and in
NetMail that the FidoNews Version List has grown to a large size.
That's the main reason Tom put the job up for volunteers.  I was
picked from the "hat," so to say...<g>

A couple of alternatives I have had suggested to me have been...

A) Split the List.  Publish one or two system lists a week,
   alternating.

B) Delete old listings.

Until the end of September I an soliciting for ideas on how to handle
consolidating the Version List.  At that time I will make a decision
and the September 30 FidoNews will show the results.  Please direct
all suggestions to 1:103/950 via NetMail.

It has also been pointed out that some of the software listed is not
really easy to find.  I would like to implement a rotating list of
Main Support Boards for Software(e.g. RA 1:1/120, Binkley 1:1/102,
etc.)   This would take up a bit of space, but it would also help
the new Sysop in finding some of the hard to get items.

The details still need to be worked out and suggestions are welcome.

--dave

