by Danny Mingle @ 1:116/9
Another Suggestion about Reducing the Size of the Nodelist



A recent topic of discussion in FidoNews has concerned how to make
the nodelist smaller.

FidoNews 8-33                  Page 5                      26 Aug 1991


I propose changing the baud rate, CM, MO, LO, V21, V22, V29, V32,
V32b, V33, V34, V42, V42b, MNP, H96, HST, MAX, PEP, CSP, XA, XB, XC,
XP, XR, XW, and XX flags to one-digit codes beginning with "1" in
each of their fields.

For example, in the Special Operating Conditions field,
"CM" would become "1" (without the quotations, of course)
"MO" would become "2"
"LO" would become "3"

and in the Modem Capabilities field,
"V21" would become "1"
"V22" would become "2"
.
.
.
"MNP" would become "A"
"H96" would become "B"
etc. etc.


I hope this clearly demonstrates what I mean about how the
numbering would start "with 1 in each of their individual fields".


These changes would be short and simple, and so is this article.  If
you send netmail, I will attempt to reply but cannot promise that you
will receive it.

